What is ECS?
Amazon ECS is a fully managed container orchestration service used to deploy, manage, and scale Docker containers.
Before ECS, DevOps engineers manually managed Docker containers on servers.

With ECS:

Write Dockerfile
      ↓
Build Image
      ↓
Push to ECR
      ↓
Deploy to ECS
      ↓
AWS Manages Containers

Why ECS?
Problems Without ECS
Container Crash
       ↓
